fields.name: Pain Relief
fields.description: Pain relievers are medicines that can help with headaches, muscle aches, arthritis, and other pains

fields.name: Diabetes
fields.description: Diabetes drugs include insulin, sulfonylureas, meglitinides, thiazolidinediones, and GLP-1 receptor agonists. These drugs help manage blood sugar levels and prevent diabetes complications

fields.name: Cholesterol
fields.description: Cholesterol drugs, also known as antihyperlipidemics, are used to treat high cholesterol levels. They include statins, bile acid sequestrants, and other drugs

fields.name: Hypertension
fields.description: Hypertension drugs, also known as antihypertensives, treat high blood pressure

fields.name: Respiratory
fields.description: Respiratory drugs treat respiratory conditions, such as asthma, bronchitis, and emphysema. They include bronchodilators, antibiotics, steroids, and mucolytics

fields.name: Allergy
fields.description: Allergy drugs include antihistamines, corticosteroid nasal sprays, and leukotriene inhibitors

fields.name: Diuretic
fields.description: Diuretic drugs, also known as water pills, increase the amount of urine the body produces. They are used to treat conditions like high blood pressure, heart failure, and fluid retention

fields.name: Steroid
fields.description: Steroids, also called corticosteroids, are anti-inflammatory medicines used to treat a range of conditions

fields.name: Amoxicillin
fields.description: Amoxicillin is a penicillin antibiotic. It is used to treat bacterial infections, such as chest infections (including pneumonia) and dental abscesses.
fields.side_effects: For most infections, you'll start to feel better in a few days. The most common side effects of amoxicillin are feeling sick (nausea) and diarrhoea. Liquid amoxicillin can stain your teeth. This does not last and is removed by brushing.

fields.name: Furosemide
fields.description: A loop diuretic used to reduce fluid retention in conditions like heart failure and kidney disease.
fields.usage_instructions: Take 20-80mg once or twice daily as prescribed.

fields.name: Spironolactone
fields.description: A potassium-sparing diuretic used to treat high blood pressure and fluid retention.

fields.name: Prednisolone
fields.description: A corticosteroid used to treat inflammation, allergies, and autoimmune disorders
fields.usage_instructions: Take 5-60mg daily as prescribed, preferably in the morning.

fields.name: Hydrochlorothiazide
fields.description: A thiazide diuretic used to treat high blood pressure and fluid retention.
fields.usage_instructions: ake 12.5-50mg once daily, preferably in the morning.

fields.name: Azithromycin
fields.description: A macrolide antibiotic used to treat bacterial infections, including respiratory and skin infections.
fields.usage_instructions: Take 500mg on day 1, followed by 250mg once daily for 4 more days.

fields.name: Warfarin
fields.description: Used to prevent blood clots in patients with deep vein thrombosis or atrial fibrillation.
fields.usage_instructions: Take as prescribed by your doctor, usually once daily.

fields.name: Insulin
fields.description: Regulates blood sugar levels in diabetic patients.
fields.usage_instructions: Inject subcutaneously as prescribed before meals.
